							<p><strong>Note:</strong> Pricing varies based on employee salary and specific requirements. Contact us for a customized quote.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ Section -->
		<section class="faq section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
					<p>Common questions about our Employer of Record services</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-list">
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Is this legal?</h3>
						<p><strong>YES</strong> ‚Äî This is 100% legal and widely practiced in Canada. Companies like Deel, Remote.com, OysterHR, and Shield GEO offer similar EOR services. We hire Canadian workers on behalf of U.S. businesses, which is completely legal as long as we do not recruit or employ U.S. workers inside the United States.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Do we need a Canadian company?</h3>
						<p><strong>NO</strong> ‚Äî That's the whole point! InfraDev Consulting acts as the employer of record. You don't need to form a Canadian corporation, register with the CRA, or set up payroll accounts. We handle all of that for you.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Do you hire remote-only workers?</h3>
						<p><strong>YES</strong> ‚Äî We specialize in remote employment. Your Canadian employees work from wherever they are located in Canada, and you manage their day-to-day work remotely.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What about immigration sponsorship?</h3>
						<p>We do not provide immigration sponsorship (TN, H1B, etc.). We only offer Canadian-based employment for workers who are already legally authorized to work in Canada.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Can you help us find candidates?</h3>
						<p>We focus on the employment and compliance side. You find the candidates you want to hire, and we facilitate the legal employment process. We are not a recruitment agency.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What happens if we need to terminate an employee?</h3>
						<p>We handle all termination processes including Record of Employment (ROE) generation, final pay, and compliance with provincial labour laws regarding notice periods and severance.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>How quickly can we onboard a new employee?</h3>
						<p>Typically within 24-48 hours once we have all required documentation. The exact timeline depends on the completeness of the employee's information and any specific provincial requirements.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What provinces do you operate in?</h3>
						<p>We can hire employees in all Canadian provinces and territories. We ensure compliance with provincial labour laws, workers' compensation (CNESST in Quebec), and all regional requirements.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Legal Disclaimer -->
		<section class="disclaimer section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="disclaimer-content">
					<h3>Legal Disclaimer</h3>
					<p>InfraDev Consulting hires employees in Canada and provides full Canadian labour compliance. We do not provide U.S. employment, immigration sponsorship, or legal tax advice. All services are provided in accordance with Canadian federal and provincial laws.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Call to Action -->
		<section class="cta section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="cta-content">
					<h2>Ready to Hire in Canada?</h2>
					<p>Book a consultation and we'll guide you through everything you need to know about cross-border hiring.</p>
					<a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Book a Cross-Border Hiring Consultation</a>
					<p class="cta-email">Or email us at <a href="mailto:marc@infradevconsulting.com">marc@infradevconsulting.com</a></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

